text: Seltjarnarnes is a town and municipality in the Capital Region of Iceland. In 2020, 4,726 people lived there. It was created in 1947. == Twin towns – sister cities == Seltjarnarnes is twinned with: * Lieto, Finland * Nesodden, Norway * Herlev, Denmark * Höganäs, Sweden == References == == Other websites == * Category:Towns in Iceland Category:Municipalities of Iceland Category:Capital Region (Iceland)
